Kaveel Singh Protesters have set buses on fire. (City of Cape Town) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Fire and rescue officials were unable to reach a burning municipal vehicle on NY1 and Govan Mbeki Road in Cape Town on Friday morning due to protests. "Officials were unable to extinguish the fire due to the volatility of protesters in the area," said City of Cape Town Fire and Rescue spokesperson Theo Layne. READ: Protests play havoc on Cape Town roads, causing major traffic headaches According to City of Cape Town traffic spokesperson Richard Coleman, there was also protest action in Govan Mbeki and Duinefontein Roads. "This led to Duinefontein being closed between The Downs and Old Landsdowne Road in both directions. We also have Govan Mbeki closed and Vygekraal Road." Coleman added that Hawston Road from Fisherhaven was closed. The Hawston community is believed to also be protesting in the area. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  